The paper discusses limitations in the application of Machine Learning (ML) to real-life problems, specifically related to the adaptation of ML models and datasets to specific applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes ways to quantify and visualise unfairness in ML-based systems, which could fall under the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses methods to mitigate unfairness, which could also be relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
